  </section>

  <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Viking wall oven repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Oven not heating — where to start?</summary>
        <p>Check 240V breaker first (free reset if tripped). Then F02 on display (RTD probe, $165-$245). Then bake element (20-30 ohms good, $265-$385). Then thermal fuse ($135-$195). Then control board ($680-$940). 80% resolve at step 2-3.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Uneven cooking one rack burns</summary>
        <p>Vari-Speed Dual Flow convection fan stalled. Bearings wear year 10-14. $385-$540 replacement, 90-min job through rear panel. Check fan blade for impact damage simultaneously — bent blade mimics motor failure.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Thermal fuse tripped</summary>
        <p>One-time safety fuse. Replacement $135-$195. But replacing without root-cause fix = will trip again. We diagnose why it overheated (RTD, thermostat, self-clean) before replacing fuse.</p>
      </details>

